 :tx/rationale "Set t-30f5d046 title=PERF-4: Introspective Observer Daemon (ADR-FOUNDATION-031, INV-FOUNDATION-015). The daemon's primary purpose is enabling C7 self-bootstrap by giving braid persistent identity and self-observation capability. Performance (<100ms status) is a consequence, not the goal. ARCHITECTURE: (1) Persistent process with Unix socket (.braid/daemon.sock). Holds Store + indexes + computed state in memory. (2) INTROSPECTIVE OBSERVATIONS: Every command generates :runtime/* datoms in W-alpha — latency-ms, cache-hit, routing-ms, store-datom-count, command-name, error-count. These use the SAME 6 ADR-029 lifecycle attributes as project knowledge connections. (3) REFLEXIVE BOUNDARIES: RuntimeBoundary type in BoundaryRegistry evaluates self-model against measurements. latency > 5s = reflexive divergence. cache-miss-rate > 0.5 = reflexive divergence. routing-cost growing faster than datom-count = reflexive divergence. (4) REFLEXIVE F(S): Include a reflexive component in F(S) — does braid's self-model match actual behavior? (5) CODE-AWARE CRB: Before creating a task, grep codebase for existing implementations. 'store cache' -> find write_index_cache in layout.rs -> 'Already implemented. Create anyway?' (6) SESSION LIFECYCLE: Auto-start on first command, auto-stop on harvest --commit. W-alpha flushed to journal on session end. (7) INCREMENTAL ROUTING: On new txn, re-score only AFFECTED tasks (those with deps/traces to changed entities), not all 256. O(k) instead of O(N). ACCEPTANCE: (A) status with daemon: <100ms. (B) :runtime/* datoms recorded per command. (C) RuntimeBoundary detects latency regression. (D) Code-aware CRB prevents duplicate task creation. (E) FEGH bridge hypotheses work on self-model. (F) Clean shutdown writes cache + flushes W-alpha. DEPENDS-ON: PERF-2. TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-031, INV-FOUNDATION-015, ADR-STORE-006, C7. FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs (new) + crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs (RuntimeBoundary)"
